# Launch Announcement – Blood Donation Camp 2026 (16 Jan 2026)

Dear Students, Faculty Members, and Staff,  

The University Health Club in collaboration with the NSS Unit is pleased to announce **“Blood Donation Camp 2026”**, a university-level initiative aimed at promoting community health and saving lives through voluntary blood donation.

Blood donation is a simple yet powerful act of social responsibility. Your participation can make a vital difference to patients in need and strengthen the spirit of service within our university community. We encourage maximum participation from all eligible members.

---

## Event Details

- **Event Title:** Blood Donation Camp 2026  
- **Organized by:** University Health Club + NSS Unit  
- **Venue:** Open Arena near Library  
- **Date:** 16 January 2026 (Friday)  
- **Time:** 10:00 AM to 4:00 PM  
- **Eligibility:** Minimum age 18 years, minimum weight 50 kg, and in good health  
- **Items to Carry:** University ID Card  
- **Registration:** On-spot registration available  

---

## Call to Action

Kindly come forward and donate blood as per your eligibility and availability, and motivate your peers to participate.

For queries, please contact **Rashi (912345678)**.

Let us unite to uphold the values of humanity, health awareness, and social responsibility through this meaningful initiative.

